# Caddyfile — TLS-terminating reverse proxy for CaseLight.
#
# Runs as the Dockerized "caddy" service (docker-compose.yml, "proxy" profile). Set APP_HOST
# in .env to your public hostname (e.g. cases.example.org). Caddy then auto-provisions and
# renews a Let's Encrypt certificate for it.
#
# Requirements to go live:
#   - DNS: an A record for APP_HOST pointing at this box's public (Elastic) IP.
#   - Security group: inbound 80 and 443 open (80 is needed for the ACME HTTP challenge + the
#     HTTP->HTTPS redirect Caddy adds automatically).
#   - APP_HOST set in .env, then: docker compose --profile proxy up -d caddy
#
# With APP_HOST unset it falls back to localhost (local use only; no public cert is requested).

{$APP_HOST:localhost} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}
